nodes.bodyText:
You could potentially:

make updateMinMaxValues accept type parameter, e.g:

private void updateMinMaxValues(Type type, Block block, int channelIndex)

and then dispatch to that method:
private void updateMinMaxValues(Block block, int channelIndex) {
  Type type = channels.get(channelIndex).type;
  if (type instanceof BigintType) {
    updateMinMaxValues(type, block, channelIndex);
  } else if (type instaneof IntType) {
    updateMinMaxValues(type, block, channelIndex);
  }
}

for selected types.
We would need to benchmark if JIT actually does indeed inline separate branches of code (resulting method could be too large)
Alternatively, we could obtain MethodHandle for updateMinMaxValues(Type type, Block block, int channelIndex) via https://docs.oracle.com/javase/8/docs/api/java/lang/invoke/MethodHandles.html#insertArguments-java.lang.invoke.MethodHandle-int-java.lang.Object...- with partially applied type argument.
In any case, this could be improvement after this PR and requires extending of benchmarks

